column2: UPDATE 1-Australia's Ten plans equity boost from News Corp's Foxtel as losses mount SYDNEY
column3: Oct 26 Australian broadcaster Ten Network Holdings Ltd plans to raise A$154 million ($111 million) by selling shares to News Corp's Australian pay TV unit and other shareholders
column4: after a licence writedown led to its third straight annual loss. ~Australia's Ten plans equity boost from News Corp's Foxtel as losses mount SYDNEY
column5: Oct 26 Australian broadcaster Ten Network Holdings Ltd said it would raise A$154 million ($111 million) by selling shares to the Australian pay TV unit of News Corp and existing shareholders as it racked up another hefty loss. ~
